cs.SD, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM

The paper deals with audiovisual fusion using deep learning techniques, which involves computer vision (extracting features from pixels) and natural language processing (classification of speech and nonlinguistic vocalisations). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves training and optimizing deep learning models, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
